THE Dar es Salaam Rotary Goat Races is set to take place in the city, a fun family- event aimed at raising funds for charitable projects. Head of Rotary Club of Oysterbay, organisers of the event, Amish Shash said the revenues generated from this year’s event will be used for various service projects of the club, mainly on environmental projects. ‘ This year’s motto ‘Arabian Dreams’, will attract new fans and previous Goat Race enthusiasts likewise. The event is fun-filled and caters for the entire family with all the amenities to keep everyone entertained,” Shash said. The Dar es Salaam Rotary Goat Races has been a staple in the annual eventcalendar for the past 18 years and one of the premier charity events in the city. This year’s event will take place on the 21st September on the Green in Oysterbay and banks on the previous assets of the races. This is the second year that the Rotary Club of Oysterbay will be holding the Event under the name of The Goat Races presented by the Rotary Club of Oysterbay. “The cause of this year would be focusing on efforts towards enriching, enhancing, and promoting service above self in our local communities,” he said. This can be through new initiatives as well as the ones that are currently underway such as scholarships, provision of facilities and education on hygiene and sanitation, peace and conflict resolution, disease prevention and treatment, water and sanitation, maternal and child health, basic education and literacy and economic and community development, he elaborated. In Tanzania, the club supports the community with a wide range of projects, among those a Community Health Initiative that organises biannual medical camps in rural and urban Tanzania.